Ah, you're assigning a reference to a `&Result`, but then you're trying to move out of it. You can't do that because `result` is just a reference. Instead, if you want the actual result, you'd need to dereference or clone it.

Try this instead:
```rust
fn run_test() -> Result<(), Box<dyn Error>> {
    let result = get_result()?;  // Use ? to propagate errors here
    // ... (use `result` directly)
}
`
This way, you're unwrapping the `Result`, moving out of it. That should fix your error.

If you actually need the value behind the reference, dereference it (`result.deref()`), but then you can't move out of it since references are immutable. Instead, you can clone it if `Result` implements `Clone`, or simply use the reference to check status without moving ownership:

```rust
fn run_test() -> Result<(), Box<dyn Error>> {
    let result: &Result<_, _> = get_result();
    match result {
        Ok(_) => println!("Test passed!"),
        Err(e) => return Err(e.to_owned()),  // Clone error to move out
    }
}
`
This way, you avoid moving out of the reference and can still propagate errors.

